parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on busy highways.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays an incorrect reading
showing more fuel than is actually available
or suddenly drops to empty
causing the vehicle to stall or shut down. The vehicle may also experience sputtering or bucking before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge displays incorrect information
vehicle stalls or hesitates
fuel light does not come on
and sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of gas, leading to unexpected engine shutdown, loss of power brakes and steering, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge shows a higher fuel level than actual
the vehicle runs out of gas despite the gauge indicating a quarter tank or more
the low fuel warning light does not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause unexpected shutdown of the vehicle, loss of power brakes and steering, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
the fuel gauge is inaccurate
the backup sensors stop working
electrical issues occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to unexpected engine shutdown and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery dies
the alternator fails to charge the battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The speedometer failure can cause the driver to unknowingly exceed the speed limit, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer shows an incorrect speed
the driver realizes they are driving slower than indicated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexplained vehicle fire can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while parked and turned off.
